display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  X\to  Y]]></fr:tex> be a morphism of finite type, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  X]]></fr:tex>, and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y=f(x)]]></fr:tex>.
    Then the following conditions are equivalent:</fr:p>
 <html:ol
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;i. &quot;">
      <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_x/\mathfrak {m}_y\mathcal {O}_x]]></fr:tex> is a finite separable extension of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[k(y)]]></fr:tex>.
    </html:li>

    
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;ii. &quot;">
      <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Omega _{X/Y}^1]]></fr:tex> is zero at <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex>.
    </html:li>

    
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;iii. &quot;">
      The diagonal morphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Delta _{X/Y}]]></fr:tex> is an open immersion on a neighbourhood of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex>.
    </html:li>

  </html:ol>

  
    
    <fr:tree
