display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  X\to  Y]]></fr:tex> be of finite type, and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  X]]></fr:tex>.
    The property of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> being étale at <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> depends only on the local homomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_{f(x)}\to \mathcal {O}_x]]></fr:tex>, and in fact only on the corresponding homomorphism for the completions.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
