xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>410</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">sga1-i.4.4</fr:addr><fr:route>sga1-i.4.4.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Corollary</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>I.4.4</fr:number><fr:parent>sga1-i.4</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Suppose that the residue extension <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[k(A)\to  k(B)]]></fr:tex> is trivial, or that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[k(A)]]></fr:tex> is algebraically closed.
    Then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B/A]]></fr:tex> is étale if and only if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\widehat {A}\to \widehat {B}]]></fr:tex> is an isomorphism.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:p>We can combine flatness with <fr:ref
addr="sga1-i.3.7"
href="sga1-i.3.7.xml"
taxon="Proposition"
number="I.3.7" />.</fr:p><fr:tree
