    <fr:p>Again, this is true individually for both "unramified" and "flat".</fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
  
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:p>This proposition shows that we can forget about the "one-off" comments in the study of morphisms of finite type that are somewhere étale.</fr:p><fr:tree
