root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>422</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">sga1-i.4.10</fr:addr><fr:route>sga1-i.4.10.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proposition</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>I.4.10</fr:number><fr:parent>sga1-i.4</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> be a flat cover of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> of degree <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> (the definition of this term deserved to figure in <fr:ref
addr="sga1-i.4.9"
href="sga1-i.4.9.xml"
taxon="Definition"
number="I.4.9" />) defined by a locally free coherent sheaf <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {B}]]></fr:tex> of algebras.
    We define, as usual, the trace homomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {B}\to \mathcal {A}]]></fr:tex> (that is, a homomorphism of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {A}]]></fr:tex>-modules, where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {A}=\mathcal {O}_Y]]></fr:tex>).
    For <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> to be étale it is necessary and sufficient that the corresponding bilinear form <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {tr}_{\mathcal {B}/\mathcal {A}}xy]]></fr:tex> define an isomorphism of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {B}]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {B}]]></fr:tex>, or, equivalently, that the <fr:em>discriminant section</fr:em>
    <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[       d_{X/Y}       = d_{\mathcal {B}/\mathcal {A}}       \in  \Gamma \big (Y,\wedge ^n\check {\mathcal {B}}\otimes _\mathcal {A}\wedge ^n\check {\mathcal {B}}\big )     ]]></fr:tex>
    is invertible, or that the discriminant ideal defined by this section is the unit ring.</fr:p>
  
    
    <fr:tree
toc="false"
